Insalltion:
====================

1) On LINUX Platforms:

	Make sure you have python and pyqt packages instlled before proceeding.

	Get the source code from http://bitbucket.org/viranch/sam or clone the repo:
	$ hg clone http://bitbucket.org/viranch/pdfedit
	Note: if the above command doesn't work, you need to install the package mercurial,
	otherwise get the code from http://bitbucket.org/viranch/pdfedit

	PDFEdit is ready to use! Just execute the pdfedit.pyw

	(Sorry, PDFEdit doesn't currently add shortcuts to the Kicker menu)

2) On Windows Platform:

	Install Python ( http://www.python.org/ftp/python/2.7/python-2.7.msi )
	and PyQt ( http://www.riverbankcomputing.co.uk/static/Downloads/PyQt4/PyQt-Py2.7-gpl-4.7.6-1.exe )
	Get the source from http://bitbucket.org/viranch/pdfedit and just double-click the "pdfedit.pyw" file.
	Contact the author in case it doesn't work.
	Otherwise, you can create shortcut to the file on your desktop for later use. :-)

